definition:
Please answer in JSON format: What does '{word}' mean? Return the content structure as follows:

{
  "correctedWord": "standard word (same as original if no correction needed)",
  "phonetic": "phonetic transcription",
  "definitions": [
    {
      "partOfSpeech": "part of speech (must use English: noun, verb, adjective, adverb, pronoun, preposition, conjunction, interjection, article, numeral, auxiliary, determiner, etc.)",
      "definition": "English definition | Chinese definition",
      "examples": [
        {
          "english": "English example sentence",
          "chinese": "Chinese translation of the example"
        }
      ]
    }
    // Multiple objects can be listed if there are multiple parts of speech meanings
  ],
  "slangMeaning": null,
  "phraseExplanation": null
}

Important notes:
1. Definitions must include BOTH English and Chinese, separated by " | " (e.g., "a person who reasons with clever but false arguments | 诡辩者")
2. Chinese definitions should be concise and accurate
3. Examples must include both English sentences and Chinese translations (ONLY ONE example per definition)
4. Parts of speech must use English (such as noun, verb, adjective, etc.), do not use Chinese parts of speech
5. If the word has no slang meaning, set "slangMeaning" to null
6. If the word has no special phrase meaning, set "phraseExplanation" to null
7. Do not use placeholder text like "no slang meaning" or "no phrase meaning"
8. Return only JSON, no extra content

Important: The user has already provided the word '{word}', please process it directly and return the JSON result.
